00:01:06.570 --> 00:01:07.790
That’s a great question.

00:01:07.790 --> 00:01:08.790
Everyone wants whiter teeth now.

00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:12.200
And there are really three main ways you can
bleach your teeth.

00:01:12.200 --> 00:01:15.750
Let’s first talk about what makes one bleaching
product better than another.

00:01:15.750 --> 00:01:18.760
So two factors determine how good a bleaching
product is.

00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:22.930
One is the percentage of hydrogen peroxide,
which is the bleaching agent in the bleaching

00:01:22.930 --> 00:01:23.930
products.

00:01:23.930 --> 00:01:28.420
Two is how well and how long that bleaching
product remains isolated on your teeth.

00:01:28.420 --> 00:01:33.040
So the first way we could bleach our teeth
is professionally done in a dental office,

00:01:33.040 --> 00:01:38.780
with a laser, it’s the highest concentration
of hydrogen peroxide, and remains isolated

00:01:38.780 --> 00:01:42.030
on your teeth for the longest amount of time,
and very well.

00:01:42.030 --> 00:01:46.960
They actually secure the bleach to your teeth
so it doesn't get over any other soft tissue.

00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:51.280
The next way is a dentist can give you take-home
custom-made trays.

00:01:51.280 --> 00:01:55.670
Now these take-home trays have also a high
percentage of hydrogen peroxide and it remains

00:01:55.670 --> 00:01:58.780
isolated on your teeth for a long duration
of time.

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:01.700
The third way you can whiten your teeth is
with over the counter products.

00:02:01.700 --> 00:02:05.890
And these products, first of all, are much
cheaper and much more affordable than in-office

00:02:05.890 --> 00:02:06.890
whitening procedures.

00:02:06.890 --> 00:02:08.610
Good for being on a budget.

00:02:08.610 --> 00:02:09.610
Yes.

00:02:09.610 --> 00:02:10.840
And they also work.

00:02:10.840 --> 00:02:15.950
The best way to pick a bleaching product over
the counter is to see which product remains

00:02:15.950 --> 00:02:17.950
isolated on your teeth the longer.

00:02:17.950 --> 00:02:22.690
So white strips is great, because there's
a technology that actually keeps the bleaching

00:02:22.690 --> 00:02:25.910
product isolated on your teeth, because that
will actually allow the bleach to remain on

00:02:25.910 --> 00:02:28.940
your teeth and allow the bleaching process
to work.

00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:29.940
Okay, fantastic.

00:02:29.940 --> 00:02:34.170
Okay, now that my teeth are finally whiter,
how do I keep them whiter?

00:02:34.170 --> 00:02:35.170
Yes.

00:02:35.170 --> 00:02:36.170
Maintenance.

00:02:36.170 --> 00:02:37.530
It’s just like having your hair dyed blonde.

00:02:37.530 --> 00:02:40.890
Once it’s dyed blonde, you have to-- you
have to maintain that color.

00:02:40.890 --> 00:02:42.530
Same thing with the color of your teeth.

00:02:42.530 --> 00:02:45.640
Once you bleach your teeth, it’s not going
to remain white forever, especially if you're

00:02:45.640 --> 00:02:48.540
having a lot of coffee, red wine that will
stain your teeth.

00:02:48.540 --> 00:02:53.950
You have to maintain using over the counter
products or like the white strips or using

00:02:53.950 --> 00:02:56.080
whitening toothpaste or whitening rinse.

00:02:56.080 --> 00:02:58.319
These all will help maintain the color of
your teeth.

00:02:58.319 --> 00:02:59.319
Okay.

00:02:59.319 --> 00:03:00.319
Now, I want to get back.

00:03:00.319 --> 00:03:01.319
You mentioned whitening toothpastes.

00:03:01.319 --> 00:03:02.319
Are they safe?

00:03:02.319 --> 00:03:03.319
Yes, absolutely.

00:03:03.319 --> 00:03:07.069
Now just to clarify, there's a difference
between whitening and bleaching.

00:03:07.069 --> 00:03:08.069
Oh, okay.

00:03:08.069 --> 00:03:11.860
So a lot of the products over the counter,
such as this whitening toothpaste, is a whitening

00:03:11.860 --> 00:03:12.860
agent.

00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:17.080
What a whitening agent is, is it will remove
surface stains to make your teeth appear whiter

00:03:17.080 --> 00:03:18.260
than they are.

00:03:18.260 --> 00:03:19.580
That's different from bleaching.

00:03:19.580 --> 00:03:22.250
A bleaching product will have hydrogen peroxide
in it.

00:03:22.250 --> 00:03:26.720
And the oxygen from the hydrogen peroxide
will oxidize these long chain stains and breaks

00:03:26.720 --> 00:03:28.680
these chains up, intrinsically.

00:03:28.680 --> 00:03:32.420
And that actually bleaches the tooth, making
the teeth lighter than they actually were.

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:35.420
So whitening will make your teeth appear whiter
by removing surface stains.

00:03:35.420 --> 00:03:37.950
And bleaching will actually make your teeth
lighter than they were.

00:03:37.950 --> 00:03:38.950
Okay, got it.

00:03:38.950 --> 00:03:42.810
So if you are a coffee drinker or a red wine
drinker, if you look for whitening products

00:03:42.810 --> 00:03:46.590
that will help to remove those stains that
are caused by those products

00:03:46.590 --> 00:03:47.590
Yes.

00:03:47.590 --> 00:03:49.710
